(5. ln the case here supposed the title conferred by a completed usucapion is rescinded or cancelled by in integrum restitutio (note on § 33 int), and the plaintiti' establishes his right by an ordinary vindicatio or Publiciana according to the precise nature olbis interest : the assumption by some writers ol an independent action (rescissoria or contraria Publi- cianae) has no foundation. The text speaks only of protection against an absent person; but the principle was applied equally in favour ol those whose property, while they were absent rei publicae causa, had been acquired per usucapionem, Dig. 4. 6. 23. 33 43. 1. r 5. pr.; cl. the note on in integrum restitutio, § 33 inl.
